The fast trains are ordered and paid for by the Ministry of Transport, and the railways will receive four billion crowns to compensate for the so-called loss of liquidity in the next year, just as they did this year. Local trains will supply the districts, and they will pay eight billion crowns in total for the next year, with the state contributing three billion crowns.
This year, regional trains are 200 million Czech crowns more expensive.
