Admiral Nelson's encounter with a polar bear as a brave 14-year-old ensign at sea who fought only with the butt of his musket is certainly a legend, but others are true.
Young bears caught swimming behind the bodies of their recently killed mothers have been taken to zoos and circuses.
A circus performance at the beginning of the 20th century showed 75 polar bears at a performance.
