All so-called counter-revolutionary activities, including light protests and critical writings, carry a risk of arrest.
Anti-government graffiti and statements are considered a serious crime.
Cuba has a growing community of bloggers, led by popular reporter Yoani Sánchez, who often describes how she and her husband are persecuted and attacked by government officials.
