Wang Weijia and her husband grew up surrounded by propaganda posters lecturing them that "Mother Earth is too tired to entertain more children" and "One more baby means one more grave."
They learned these lessons so well that when Shanghai government officials, who had suddenly begun to change tack this summer, owing to the low birth rate and aging population, and encouraged young couples to have more than one child, their answer was immediate and definitive: "Absolutely not."
