There is nothing left for a second child, said Wang, 31, a human resources manager with an 8-month-old son.
More than 30 years after the introduction of the one-child policy in China, which produced two generations of notoriously plump, spoiled only children affectionately known as "little emperors," a population crisis is looming in the country.
