New vehicle inspection programmes
In these days of severe weather and accidents, it is not only the car workshops that deserve
Every day, thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are towed to repairers, where an expert assesses the damage caused and the cost of repairs.
Not a single accident is the same and calculating the cost of parts and hours of work can be a lengthy and complicated task.
The manual calculation of repair costs ranging from 20,000 to 30,000 euros, including parts and working hours, can take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the support of the latest computer science tools, it is a matter of minutes
This is why almost 100% of surveyors use this type of system.
The service and application providers for accident assessment and repair collect the information they receive from the manufacturers for subsequent processing and offering it to their customers in the form of a useful programme.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all expert opinions are based on its products.
The other two companies competing in the market for evaluation and report preparation tools are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by the manufacturers is anything but easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Audatex sales manager, 63 manufacturers and importers are involved, each of whom provides the information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is increasing, to the point that in the last five years there have been more versions, variants and motors on the market than in the whole of the previous fifteen years.
As soon as a new car comes on the market, companies start to work.
It is an arduous task, because each of the thousands and thousands of vehicle parts has to be catagolized and its price entered.
In addition, an "intelligent" graphic image is created of each model, on which different parts of the vehicle can be "clicked."
If it is a much-sold model, the work can be completed in a week if the process proceeds swiftly.
If it is a less common car, it can take up to three or four months. Currently, Audatex has full information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, they have information about the Porsche models, for example, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
In terms of the number of vehicles on the roads, it is over 99%.
Audatex has eight distributed centres around the world (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) for documentation and database production, each of which specialises in specific brands.
The national headquarters are located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics specialists) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros a year in the development of these databases.
Every month they record 2.5 million data and their customers receive updates every other day.
The elaboration of this enormous flow of information enables companies to use it in different ways and thus to offer different products.
The most common use is for repairs and repairs, but depending on the country there are also tools for managing scrap parts or calculating the file or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that informs about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer this service in Spain, but in the United States.
When reviewing the products Audatex offers, it is easy to get an overview of the kind of support it provides to industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, the star of which is AudaPlus, a standard accident assessment solution for surveyors.
It includes vehicles, motorcycles as well as light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it includes the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the painting prices.
This tool is paid for according to the intended use, i.e. for each expert opinion.
It will be most expensive for customers who use it rarely, no more than ten times a month, namely 5.75 euros per month.
